Package: MyoScore
Title: A Genetically-Informed Transcriptomic Scoring System for Quantifying
    Human Skeletal Muscle Health
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Huahua", "Zhong", email = "huahuazhong@fudan.edu.cn",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7852-3982"))
Description: Calculate the MyoScore (Genetic Muscle Health Score, GMHS) from
    bulk RNA-seq raw count data. MyoScore quantifies muscle health across five
    genetically-driven dimensions (Strength, Mass, LeanMuscle, Youth, Resilience)
    based on GWAS-TWAS integration of 28 muscle-related phenotypes. Provides
    preprocessing (CPM normalization), dimension-level and composite scoring
    (0-100 scale), and visualization utilities (radar charts, grouped boxplots).
